songs.title: PSYCHO
songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
She know how the pain go
Shawty was a nympho
It wasn't all her mom's fault
Situations, situations
He got caught up with the narcos
In and out of residentials
Forgot what he was meant for
Coulda had it all in high school

[Pre-Chorus]
But somethings we can't change
There's no one left to blame
Act like we're okay
But we keep lying to ourselves

[Chorus]
Might go, might go
I might go fuckin' psycho
Baby I'm feeling spiteful
Near the edge, all in my head like
Might go, might go
I might go fuckin' psycho
Baby I'm feeling spiteful
Near the edge, all in my head like

[Interlude]
I don't give a fuck about nothing, man
I'm dead out here, man
I can't function

[Verse 2]
I know how the pain go
Hurting people I know
Steve said I gotta lay low
My karma catching up though
It's getting hard to fake it each time
I tell myself that this the last time
I'm numbing my frustration
Situations, situations

[Pre-Chorus]
There's somethings we can't change
There's no one left to blame
Act like we're okay
But we keep lying to ourselves

[Chorus]
Might go, might go
I might go fuckin' psycho
Baby I'm feeling spiteful
Near the edge, all in my head like
Might go, might go

Baby I'm feeling spiteful
